flasher is a CLI spaced repetition flashcard program.

Right now, flasher is a loosely held together couple of ksh shell scripts
which make calls to sqlite3.

pegs is a sample question and answer file of pegs for the major system
memory method.

When I get (or anybody else gets) around to it, this should
really use the supermemo2 algorithm described at the bottom of
http://www.supermemo.com/english/ol/sm2.htm

cf:
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spaced_repetition
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mnemonic_major_system
http://www.supermemo.com/english/ol/sm2.htm
